GXFP5130 Linux fingerprint support

This integration was assembled from reverse-engineering work and local testing
on a Huawei MateBook X Pro 2024 with ACPI device GXFP5130:00.

Credits:

- Void755/gxfp_linux_driver for the GXFP5130 eSPI kernel transport.
- Void755/gxfpmoc for Goodix MOC userspace protocol, TLS/PSK handling,
  provisioning, recovery, and capture primitives.
- AlexDaichendt/sil6250-linux for matcher code and reverse-engineering notes.
- uunicorn/open-fprintd for the standalone backend architecture.

No PSKs, provisioning blobs, traces, raw fingerprint images, or enrolled
templates are included in this repository.
